diagram.documentation: This top-level activity diagram illustrates the primary functions and workflow of our autonomous orbital manufacturing system. The diagram begins with the initial node and progresses through eight key activities: (1) Conduct Autonomous Orbital Manufacturing Operations, (2) Maintain Operational Availability of Orbital Platform, (3) Ensure Compliance with Regulatory and Safety Standards, (4) Manage Resources and Logistics for Orbital Manufacturing, (5) Fault Recovery and Remote Override, (6) Monitor and Analyze System Performance, (7) On-Orbit Assembly, Activation, and Upgrade, and (8) Manage Orbital Position and Attitude. These activities are interconnected by control flows, representing the sequence and dependencies of operations. The diagram also incorporates object flows to represent the movement of materials and data through the system. Parallel processing is depicted where appropriate, such as simultaneous monitoring and manufacturing activities. The activity diagram concludes with a final node representing the completion of a manufacturing cycle. This visual representation provides stakeholders with a clear overview of the system's operational flow and the relationships between its core functions
